The CLARK AND WILSON LUMBER COMPANY OF DELAWARE, Appellant, v. FIRST AND AMERICAN NATIONAL BANK OF DULUTH, and S. A. McAllister, Receiver of Nehalem Timber & Logging Co., Appellees. No. 9296. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Sept. 22, 1939. Charles A. Hart and Carey, Hart, Spencer & McCulloch, all of Portland, Or., for appellant. Sidney Teiser and Teiser & Keller, all of Portland, Or., for appellee McAllister, etc. Wilbur, Beckett, Howell & Oppenheimer, of Portland, Or., for appellee Bank.

Before GARRECHT, HANEY, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
